sentences: Shubha Mudgal (born 1 January 1959) is an Indian singer of Hindustani classical music.
She has received the Padma Shri in 2000.
Shubha Mudgal started performing as a Hindustani classical singer in the 1980s, and gained a certain reputation as a talented singer.
In the 1990s, she started experimenting with other forms of music, including pop and fusion varieties.
If you are a musician, how can you say, 'this one is from devotional poetry, so I am not going to sing it."'
In 2019, she also turned into a fictional writer with her debut book titled 'Looking for Miss Sargam: Stories of Music and Misadventure'.
